The paper is primarily focused on face recognition using deep neural networks, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The study also involves the use of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) techniques. Additionally, the paper discusses the potential security implications of false positive face detections, which could be relevant to the cryptography and security (cs.CR) sub-category. Finally, the study also touches on the concept of human-level performance in face recognition, which could be relevant to the human-computer interaction (cs.HC) sub-category.
